Myanmar demanded that the Thai government strictly control refugee camps on the Thai side of the border between the two countries.
These camps house anti-Myanmar government armed groups and their families.
A government official claimed these camps were used for military and terrorist training.
Under its military junta, Myanmar has continued to be a principal source heroin and a source of methamphetamine.
It was denied US anti-drug certification in the 2000 release of its annual anti-drug certification report.
